><A HREF="gc.htm"> Of God and His Creatures</a><hr><p>
This is what Averroes is represented as saying in Chap. <a 
href="gc2_60.htm">LX</a>, which see for explanations. <i>Et intelligit 
Aristoteles per intellectum passibilem ipsam virtutem cogitativam</i> 
is Averroes s comment on the <b>path&ecirc;tikos nous phthartos</b> of 
<i>De anima</i>, III, v, 3. Alexander had taken the <b>path&ecirc;tikos 
nous</b> to be the potential intellect. St Thomas is Averroist on this 
point.  
